By using the <%= link_to "highlight gem", "https://github.com/simplabs/highlight" %> and a bit of css trick, you can have a colorful code section in your rails app page as below. 
<%= link_to article_path(article) do %>
	Read More <i class="icon-signin"></i>
<% end %>
<% code = "#Believe me this is a class without syntax error
class Constant
  def self.gender
    {:female => 'gal', :male => 'guy', :else => '*@#\$'}
  end
end" %>
<%= render 'code_section', :title => "/path/to/your/class.rb", :code => code, :lang => :rb %>